article.headline: Lipscomb 80, S.C.-Upstate 66
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Josh Slater scored 25 points to help Lipscomb hold off South Carolina-Upstate 80-66 on Saturday night. The Bisons (7-7, 4-1 Atlantic Sun Conference), who won their third straight game, are tied for first in the league. Despite foul trouble, center Adnan Hodzic added 11 points for Lipscomb to keep his double-figures scoring streak alive at 41 consecutive games -- the longest in the nation -- with James Florence of Mercer next at 37. Bisons forward Brandon Brown was sidelined with a shoulder injury during the Saturday morning shootaround and is expected to return Monday. Lipscomb never trailed after opening the game with a 3-pointer from Michael Teller. Johnny Lee added 12 points. The Spartans (1-14, 1-5), who had 20 turnovers, cut a 14-point deficit to 61-55 with 5:08 left in the game, but could get no closer. Nick Schneiders led S.C.-Upstate with 19 points.
